==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pipa
<hw>Pi*pa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pipas</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
Surinam toad (<spn>Pipa Americana</spn>), noted for its peculiar
breeding habits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The male places the eggs on the back of the female,
where they soon become inclosed in capsules formed by the thickening of
the skin. The incubation of the eggs takes place in the capsules, and
the young, when hatched, come forth with well developed legs.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pipage</ent>⟦br⟧
